(635, '1746..rer', '', '', 'C -------------- EARLY VERSION NOW REPLACED ----------------', 'Recueil de romans historiques', 'Londres, #21746 (I-IV) - 1747 (V-VIII), 8t. in-12, viii + 326, iv + 254, iv + 268, iv + 339, v (pour iv) + 256, iv + 290, iv + 288, v (pour iv) + 275p.', 'London-B] Paris-A] Paris-NF ----- VGM SAW ARSENAL 8oBL 28935 (1-4). GIVES PAGINATION AS ON OA LOWE\'S NOTES, EXCEPT FOR T.V: v (pour iv) + 256; AND T. VIII: v (pour iv) + 275p.. VGM SENDS OA LOWE\'S NOTES: Londres, 1746 (I-III) - 1747 (IV-VIII), 8t. in-12, viii + 326, iv +254, iv +268, iv + 339, v + 256, iv + 290, iv + 288, v + 275p. NOTE ADDITION OF PRELIMINARY PAGES. AM IN FACT SAW BN\'S T.VIII WHEN Y2.61716 WAS DELIVERED IN ERROR ON 11SEP84. I DID NOT NOTE THE ERROR OV v FOR iv - BUT MY PAGINATION DETAILS CONFIRM THIS AS I MARKED i-v + /1/-275 ... WITH NO BLANK PAGE MARKED AFTER THE v. 02/07/02: microfiche of t. VIII (from Y2-6695) delivered in error for t. I when I was checking Middle Ages. Same error of v for iv. RLF: check 1744, 4t. Munich-E. Londres, 1744, 4 t. Munich=E / P. O Gall 1853 / Londres, 1746-?? ? t. ??? (A, BL, BN, ADD Munich-E) / P. O. Gall 1854 / AM\'S NOTES FROM GOETTINGEN CATALOGUE GIVE FROM FAB. ROM. III. 246 AND 261 THIS TITLE LONDRES, 1746-1747. Göttingen 1746-1747*** RLF: Corvey-Paderborn] HAS PRINCEPS, 8T. IN-12. Höxter-FC 8t. **** RLF: Londres, 1747 (Taylor]:I-IV). I. BEGINS WITH CONNETABLE ... AND IV ENDS WITH MARIE D\'ANJOU. CAN WE CONFIRM THE DATE. IF CORRECT THIS IS A REEDITION / REISSUE. Oxford-TI 1747 I-IV ***** The Taylorian] has a 1747 set I-IV - all dated 1747. It would appear that there were several editions. Needs further checking. Did all eight tomes in fact appear in 1746? RLF: LENGLET-DUFRESNOY, Recuil de romans historiques, Londres, 1747, 8 vol. in-12 *Nîmes: I-IV, VI-VIII #8843). Nîmes-M 1747I-IV, V-VIII RLF: Recueil de romans historiques, Londres, 1746*, 4t. in-12, ?, ?, ?, ?, v + 256, iv + 290, iv + 288, v+ 275p. ( Vienne]:Vi-VIII* - all dated 17