(969, '1781.DID.bij', 'DIDEROT, Denis', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1781001', 'Les bijoux indiscrets', '', '', 'Au Monomotapa, #1s.n., #1781, in-12, 220, 248p.', 'Cambridge-TC, Göttingen-NSU, Hamburg-SU, Ko/benhavn-K, Lausanne-Dorigny-CU], Lyon-M], Moskva-RG, New Haven-YU, Oxford-B, Oxford-T, Paris-NF, Stockholm-K], Washington-C, Wien-ON], Adams BI14 ------- ORIGINAL SOURCE: Brissart Cazin, sa vie et ses éditions, 1863, GIVES 1685* BI14 /1781/ Les bijoux indiscrets, Au Monomotapa, in-12, 220, 248p. Cazin. QUOTES BNF Rés Smith-Lesouef 1341/42) ... BNCC: Au Monomotapa, (Paris, 1748), 2t. in-12 AT SMITH LESOUEF R-1341/42. FW GIVES BL* 12518.a.6 (ISN\'T THIS 1771????) FW:\'L\'édition appelée A dans la dernière édition des ==OEuvres== de Diderot\' /DIECKMANN, PROUST, VARLOOT, 1978./: 220, 248p./ (Amsterdam, Göttingen, BL, Lyon, Bodley, Taylor, Rouen). ROUEN VIA CCFR GIVES 1756 AND 1772, NOT THIS EDITION. FW EXAMINED EDITION A, NOTES ELEMENTS THAT SUGGEST CAZIN, POINTS OUT THAT THE TEXT IS IN TWO PARTS (?? as before 1753) AND SUGGEST IT IS PERHAPS THE 1752 EDITION NOTED BY D\'HEMERY. NOT THE ORIGINAL EDITION. PERHAPS THE EDITION PUBLISHED BY MACHUEL AT ROUEN IN 1752. AMSTERDAM-U ENTRY GIVES NO DETAILS *RLF: 1749 REEDITION? RLF 19APR94: Au Monomotapa, s.d. /1749 says De Win/, pet. in-12, /ix/ + 220, 248p. (DeWin]*). IN FACT 1781? RLF: Au Monomotapa, s.d., 2t. pet. in-12, /6/ + 220, 248p. (Copenhague-BR]). CAZIN STYLE, WITH GILT SIDES. RLF: Monomotapa, s.d., 2t. in-12, 220, 248p. (Stockholm]). AM HAS PHOTOCOPIES. TITLE PAGE: LES/ BIJOUX/ ==INDISCRETS.==/ (single rule)/ TOME PREMIER./ (single rule)/ (print fleuron)/ ==AU MONOMOTAPA.==. RLF: Au Monomotapa, s. d. /1748?/ , in-12, 370p. ( DLC+:I) DLC gathered in sixes: e. g. E1-E6, but some gatherings are irregular. DLC CATALOGUE SAYS 220, 248p. Jones CCKW: BN* SMITH LESOUEF R-1342-43 (pagination from ADAMS), Lausanne-Dorigny-C (GOOGLE VT), Göttingen-NSU, Hamburg-SU, Moskva-RG, Wien-ON V