(1132, '1751.LAP.voy', 'LA PORTE, abbé Joseph de', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1751001', 'Voyage au sejour des ombres', 'A madame D***, seconde édition, revu^e~, corrigée & augmentée', '', 'La Haye & Paris, #1s.n., #21751, 2t. in-12, 215, 216p.', 'Canberra-NLA, Den Haag-K], London-B, Montauban-M, Paris-NF], Jones, Q ----- *ANL UNDER autre monde BUT EDITION GIVEN AS 2 ed. revu^e & augmentée SO KEEP HERE. *DEN HAAG-K HAS THE PRINTED TITLE PAGE. *LONDON-B ACCORDING TO OL ALSO HAS THE PRINTED TITLE PAGE x NYPL DOESN\'T. HAS ENGRAVED tp 1752 SO PUT IN autre monde 1752 *PARIS-NF Z-28951 HAS PRINTED TP PLUS ENGRAVED 1753 x WIEN HAS ONLY 1753 ENGRAVED TITLE, SO PUT IN Autre monde 1753. BN Z-28951 HAS ... SECONDE EDITION ... PLUS ENGRAVED TP DATED 1753 BN Z.28046-47 HAS ADDITIONAL ENGRAVED TITLE PAGE: Londres & Paris, 1753. 1. THE CATALOGUE SAYS THAT NUMM 82202 AND 82203 ARE Z-20846 (AND PRESUMABLY 20847). ON THE GALLICA ENTRY NO SIGN OF A SHELF NUMBER AND NO SIGN OF 1751 TEXT TITLE PAGE... M.D.CC.II+I = III. Z.28952 SEEN: IDENTICAL ENGRAVED TITLE PAGE, BUT ON IT THE DATE REMAINS AS M. DCC. LII. (AND AN EXTRA I. HAS NOT BEEN ADDED). HENCE THIS APPEARS AS 1752. NO SECOND TITLE PAGE REMAINS. THE TEXT APPEARS TO BE IDENTICAL WITH Z.28951. 8-RJ-2106 IS LISTED WITH THIS ENTRY. OL SAYS BL CATALOGUE GIVES 2e édition 1751, BUT TITLE PAGE IS MISSING (?) AND REPACED BY Voyage en l\'autre monde 1753. CHECK BL* RLF: REFERENCE WITHOUT LOCATION (CHECK SLIP); Mannheim-Desbillons], NN, Vienne, Büdingen MANNHEIM CATALOGUE GIVES Londres & Paris, 1752 ill. Haupttitelbl. IT CAME UP IN CCKW ANYWAY. Saint-Pétersbourg 1751 TO COME. BPLSS SUGGESTS FIRST PART IS Voyage au séjour des ombres AND SECOND PART IS: Voyage en l\'autre monde ... CCKW seconde édition: Montauban-M (séjour, 1751, no mention of extra pt); Den Haag-K (séjour, 1751 ptg 1753);', 'La seconde partie, dans les exemplaires que nous avons vus, a comme titre courant: ==Voyage en l\'autre monde ou