(969, '1781.DID.bij', '1781', 'Diderot', 'Denis', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1781001', 'Les bijoux indiscrets', '', '', 'Au Monomotapa, #1s.n., #1781, in-12, 220, 248p.', 'Cambridge-TC, Göttingen-NSU, Hamburg-SU, Ko/benhavn-K, Lausanne-Dorigny-CU], Lyon-M], Moskva-RG, New Haven-YU, Oxford-B, Oxford-T, Paris-NF, Stockholm-K], Washington-C, Wien-ON], Adams BI14 ------- ORIGINAL SOURCE: Brissart Cazin, sa vie et ses éditions, 1863, GIVES 1685* BI14 /1781/ Les bijoux indiscrets, Au Monomotapa, in-12, 220, 248p. Cazin. QUOTES BNF Rés Smith-Lesouef 1341/42) ... BNCC: Au Monomotapa, (Paris, 1748), 2t. in-12 AT SMITH LESOUEF R-1341/42. FW GIVES BL* 12518.a.6 (ISN\'T THIS 1771????) FW:\'L\'édition appelée A dans la dernière édition des ==OEuvres== de Diderot\' /DIECKMANN, PROUST, VARLOOT, 1978./: 220, 248p./ (Amsterdam, Göttingen, BL, Lyon, Bodley, Taylor, Rouen). ROUEN VIA CCFR GIVES 1756 AND 1772, NOT THIS EDITION. FW EXAMINED EDITION A, NOTES ELEMENTS THAT SUGGEST CAZIN, POINTS OUT THAT THE TEXT IS IN TWO PARTS (?? as before 1753) AND SUGGEST IT IS PERHAPS THE 1752 EDITION NOTED BY D\'HEMERY. NOT THE ORIGINAL EDITION. PERHAPS THE EDITION PUBLISHED BY MACHUEL AT ROUEN IN 1752. AMSTERDAM-U ENTRY GIVES NO DETAILS *RLF: 1749 REEDITION? RLF 19APR94: Au Monomotapa, s.d. /1749 says De Win/, pet. in-12, /ix/ + 220, 248p. (DeWin]*). IN FACT 1781? RLF: Au Monomotapa, s.d., 2t. pet. in-12, /6/ + 220, 248p. (Copenhague-BR]). CAZIN STYLE, WITH GILT SIDES. RLF: Monomotapa, s.d., 2t. in-12, 220, 248p. (Stockholm]). AM HAS PHOTOCOPIES. TITLE PAGE: LES/ BIJOUX/ ==INDISCRETS.==/ (single rule)/ TOME PREMIER./ (single rule)/ (print fleuron)/ ==AU MONOMOTAPA.==. RLF: Au Monomotapa, s. d. /1748?/ , in-12, 370p. ( DLC+:I) DLC gathered in sixes: e. g. E1-E6, but some gatherings are irregular. DLC CATALOGUE SAYS 220, 248p. Jones CCKW: BN* SMITH LESOUEF R-1342-43 (pagination from ADAMS), Lausanne-Dorigny-C (GOOGLE VT), Göttingen-NSU, Hamburg-SU, Moskva-RG, Wien-ON VT, Lyon-M VT GOOGLE, Oxford-B, Oxford-T ADD: Au Monomotap /Reims, Cazin, 1781), 2v. ill. 13 cm 12o FOUND IN YALE CATALOGUE (acquired July 18 2011!) DONE STOCKHOLM-K] (PHOTOCOPY) DONE CHECK COPENHAGEN-K. CATALOGUE GIVES Monomatopa* ? s.a., 2bd ill, BUT NO OTHER DETAILS. RLF SAY IT, SAYS CAZIN STYLE, GILT SIDES, SO INCLUDE. DONE. ADD DLC, Jones. DONE CAMBRIDGE-TC SAYS 1785, BUT NO USEFUL DETAILS. PROBABLY THIS EDITION. DOES ADAMS GIVE Cambridge FOR 1781?', 'Édition Cazin. Brissart-Binet (1863) p.128, donne la date de M.DCC.LXXXV pour une version dont nous n\'avons pas trouvé d\'exemplaire. Cambridge-U et Washington-C proposent également une date de / 1785/.'),
(970, '1797.DID.bij', '1797', 'Diderot', 'Denis', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1797001', 'Les bijoux indiscrets', '', '', 'Paris, #1tous les [marchands de nouveautés, #21797, 2 part. in-18, 177, 199p.', 'Lille-M, Lyon-M, National Trust-S, Trier-S, Dawson (1985) 79 t.I, ----- ORIGINAL SOURCES: Kornik], Krimice] BI15 1797 Les bijoux indiscrets, par Diderot, A Paris, chez tous les marchands de nouveautés, 1797, in-18, 167, 189p. DJA Plus Lille BM, Lyon BM ... RLF: Paris, chez tous les marchands de nouveautés, 1797, 2t. in-18, 177, 199p. (R. Dawson]:I). ALSO A REFERENCE TO THIS REEDITION IN REYNAUD, COL. 130, REPORTS RD. RLF: Paris, marchands de nouveautés, 1797, 2 part. in-12, 177, 199p. (Kornik]). RLF: Paris, chez tous les marchands de nouveautés, 1797, 2t. in-18, 177 /178/, 199 /200/p. (Dawson:I). RLF: Paris, 1789, 2? in-?, 177, 199p. (Darmstadt-Catal. Schlierm. ex. perdu). CCKWL Lille-M, Lyon-M, National Trust-S(altram), Tier-S', ''),
