(1137, '1753.LAP.voy', '1753', 'La porte', 'abbé Joseph de', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Vous m\'avez tellement accoutumé à vous voir, Madame, & à vous entendre, que je n\'eusse assurément jamais pu^ soutenir une absence de huit jours, si elle n\'eu^t été causée par un Voyage entrepris par votre ordre.', '', '', '1753002', 'Voyage en l\'autre monde', 'Ou nouvelles litteraires de celui-cy', '', 'La Haye & Paris, #1s.n., #21753, 2t. in-12, 215, 216p.', 'Ann Arbor-UM, Cambridge-HU, Cambridge-U, Clermont-Ferrand-MJ, Dijon-M, Edinburgh-NS, Edinburgh-U, Ithica-CU, London-B, London-SE, Manchester-U, Nîmes-CA, Paris-A, Paris-NF], Paris-S:I, Riverside-UC, Toulouse-M, Wien-ON], B ----- ORIGINAL SOURCES: A, B BN Z-28951 HAS ... SECONDE EDITION ... PLUS ENGRAVED TP DATED 1753 THIS IS REPORTED IN 1751 2e EDITION. >>>>> BN Z.28046-47 HAS ADDITIONAL ENGRAVED TITLE PAGE: Londres & Paris, 1753. 1. THE CATALOGUE SAYS THAT NUMM 82202 AND 82203 ARE Z-20846 (AND PRESUMABLY 20847). ON THE GALLICA ENTRY NO SIGN OF A SHELF NUMBER AND NO SIGN OF 1751 TEXT TITLE PAGE... M.D.CC.II+I = III. <<<<< Z.28952 SEEN: IDENTICAL ENGRAVED TITLE PAGE, BUT ON IT THE DATE REMAINS AS M. DCC. LII. (AND AN EXTRA I. HAS NOT BEEN ADDED). HENCE THIS APPEARS AS 1752. NO SECOND TITLE PAGE REMAINS. THE TEXT APPEARS TO BE IDENTICAL WITH Z.28951. 8-RJ-2106 IS LISTED WITH THIS ENTRY. BN* Z.28951 AND BL* ACCOUNTED FOR IN 1751001 BN Z.28951. ## SEEN 94/06/07:: grav. + pt. gravée: VOYAGE/ en l\'Autre/ Monde, ou/ ==NOUVELLES==/ ==LITTERAIRES==/ De Celui-cy/ A LONDRES/ ==et se trouve à PARIS==/ M. DCC. LIII. /IT LOOKS AS THOUGH THE LAST I. HAS BEEN ADDED? IN INK? ON THE ENGRAVED PLATE? OR WAS IT JUST BADLY FORMED TO START WITH/ + t.p. typographique: VOYAGE/ AU SEJOUR/ DES OMBRES./ -----/ ==A MADAME D. ***/ -----/ SECONDE E\'DITION,/ revu^e~,corrigée & augmentée./ ==PREMIERE PARTIE.==/ (fleuron)/ A LA HAYE,/ ET A PARIS./ ======/ M. DCC. LI. !! 12, 12 ... *3-215 + /216/, Fautes à corriger